M1 microkernel
==============

What is this?
-------------

M1 is a microkernel operating system. It provides core mechanisms for address
space isolation, inter-process communication, and scheduling. All other system
services - drivers, filesystems, network stacks, etc - run as isolated 
userspace servers that communicate through message passing.


Requirements
------------

* nasm
* i686-elf-gcc
* i686-elf-ld
* grub-mkrescue
* qemu-system-i386


Building
--------

The build script expects the cross toolchain to be under $HOME/opt/cross. To
build the kernel components:

	bash build.sh

To remove build artifacts:

	make clean

For more information on building the cross toolchain, see:

	https://wiki.osdev.org/GCC_Cross-Compiler


Running
-------

To run it in QEMU:

	make run


Project Layout
--------------

arch/      Architecture-specific code
boot/      Kernel initialization code
dev/       In-kernel device drivers
include/   Kernel headers
iso/       Bootloader configurations
kernel/    Core microkernel services
libk/      Shared kernel code
loader/    ELF loader
mm/        Memory management
uapi/      Shared kernel/user API
userspace/ Userspace programs